00:37:06.700 --> 00:37:08.710
And that's what this allows
me to calculate.

00:37:08.710 --> 00:37:13.720
Is how much do I
get in the end.

00:37:13.720 --> 00:37:16.350
So it's very handy.

00:37:16.350 --> 00:37:22.420
You can also see, if I go all
the way to the limit where the

00:37:22.420 --> 00:37:27.020
mole fraction in the liquid at
the end is equal to what it

00:37:27.020 --> 00:37:32.170
was in the gas when I started,
what that says is that there's

00:37:32.170 --> 00:37:34.960
no more gas left any more.

00:37:34.960 --> 00:37:39.490
In other words, these two
things are equal.

00:37:39.490 --> 00:37:44.580
If I go all the way to the point
where I've got all the,

00:37:44.580 --> 00:37:49.630
this is the amount I started
with, in the pure gas phase,

00:37:49.630 --> 00:37:51.920
now I keep raising
